ExecDesc.value: Microsoft MPEG-4 Codec Remote Code Execution (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A code execution vulnerability has been reported in Microsoft's MPEG-4 Codec. The vulnerability is due to an integer overflow while processing certain values in an ASF media file. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to process a malicious file. This can result in remote code execution in the context of the vulnerable application.
